				<div class="c-issue-toc__article-collapse-inner">
					<p>The Anthropocene Project hosted by the Haus de Kulturen der Welt in Berlin is a two-year project considering from the vantage point of art and science the hypothesis that humankind is a geological force. The last exhibition of the project, <em>The Anthropocene Project. A Report</em>, is the focus of attention here and it can be seen as part of a broader tendency to create exhibitions that are platforms for discussing and sharing urgent concerns through a series of research and artistic events. But a challenge that such research exhibitions meet, is to balance information and aesthetics, science and art.</p>
